content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 22 ยง 141.5 - Procedure in an IDV and DV parts

State Regulations
(a) Unless otherwise authorized or
required by law, no case transferred from another court to the Supreme Court
and referred for disposition to an IDV part thereof may be consolidated with
any other case pending before such IDV part. (b) Each case transferred from another
court to the Supreme Court and referred for disposition to an IDV part thereof, and each case transferred from another court to the Supreme Court or County

Court where a DV part is established and referred for disposition to a DV part
thereof, shall be subject to the same substantive and procedural law as would
have applied to it had it not been transferred, and no party thereto shall be
required to pay any fee for the assignment of an index number thereto upon such
transfer. Notes
